). Very similar to ♀ , but smaller (body length 59.0–65.0 mm). Eyes distinctly projecting hemispherically. Abdominal sternites II–VII dull yellow. Vomer with the basal half broad, then abruptly narrowed to form an elongate, slender and gently up-curving terminal hook. Poculum flat with the posterior margin broad and roundly angular, yellow and surrounded by a black line.
